al Conference on Telecommunication, Electronic and Computer Engineering, Historical City of Melaka, Malaysia, October 22-24.\nPariwat, T. and Seresangtakul, P. (2019). Thai Finger-Spelling Sign Language Recognition Employing PHOG and Local Features with KNN. The International Journal of Advances in Soft Computing and its Application, 11(3), November, pp. 94-107.\nChuong, D. N. and Seresangtakul, P. (2019). Semi-Automatic Word-Aligned Tool for Thai-Vietnamese Parallel Corpus Construction. In 2019 16th International Joint Conference on Computer Science and Software Engineering (JCSSE), Amari Pattaya, Chonburi, Thailand, July 10-12, pp.121-125.\nKlangprapunt, P. and Seresangtakul, P. (2019). An Information Integration System to Continuing of Care Case study Nongsung Hospital, Mukdahan Thailand. In 2019 16th International Joint Conference on Computer Science and Software Engineering (JCSSE), Amari Pattaya, Chonburi, Thailand, July 10-12, pp. 55-60.\nSeresangtakul, P. and Unlee, P. (2019). Thai-Isarn Dialect Parallel Corpus Construction for Machine Translation. In 2019 11th International Conference on Knowledge and Smart Technology (KST), Novotel Phuket Vintage Park, Phuket, Thailand, January 23-26, pp. 121-125.\nJanyoi, P.  and Seresangtakul, P. (2018). Isarn Dialect Speech Synthesis using HMM with syllable-context features. ECTI Transactions on Computer and Information Technology (ECTI-CIT), 12(2), pp. 81-89.\nSaipech, P. and Seresangtaku, P. (2018). Automatic Thai Subjective Examination using Cosine Similarity. In 2018 The 5th International Conference on Advanced Informatics: Concept Theory and Applications (ICAICTA), Beyond Resort, Krabi, Thailand, August 14-17, pp. 214-218.\nThaiklang, S. and Seresangtakul, P. (2018). Isarn Dharma Handwritten Character Recognition Using Neural Network and Support Vector Machine. In The 14th International Conference on Computing and Information Technology, Shangri-La Hotel, Chiang Mai, Thailand, July 5-6, pp. 197-205.\nSangkla, K. an